A closed orbit $$\Gamma \subset \R^n$$ of $$\dot{x} = f(x)$$ is called

* //(Lyapunov) stable// if for any $$\varepsilon > 0$$ there exists $$\delta > 0$$ such that as soon as $$d(y,\Gamma) \coloneqq \min_{x_0 \in \Gamma} \|y - x_0\| < \delta,$$ we have $$d(x(t;0,y),\Gamma) < \varepsilon$$ for all $$t \ge 0.$$

* //Asymptotically stable// if it is stable and additionally $$\lim_{t \to \infty} d(x(t;0,y),\Gamma) = 0.$$

