''Theorem.''
If all multipliers (except for $$\mu_n = 1$$) of the linearized system for a given periodic solution satisfy $$|\mu_j|<1,$$ then the corresponding (periodic) closed orbit $$\Gamma$$ is asymptotically stable.

Moreover, all nearby solutions $$x(t;0,y)$$ with $$d(y,\Gamma) < \delta$$ possess an //asymptotic phase// $$c \in \R$$ such that
$$
d(x(t;0,y),x_0(t+c)) \xrightarrow[t\to\infty]{} 0.
$$

